cs.RO, cs.HC, cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper is about hand guidance of robots, specifically using an AR device to extend hand guidance to robots lacking joint-torque sensors. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper discusses the use of an AR device (Microsoft Hololens) to aid in robot programming and increase situational awareness of humans working with robots. 
- cs.GR (Graphics): The paper uses a registration algorithm to match a robot model to the spatial mesh, which involves graphics and computer vision techniques. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper uses the hand tracking capabilities of the Hololens to calculate the position of the hands relative to the robot, which involves computer vision techniques. 
- cs.SD (Sound): Although less likely, the paper mentions the use of sound feedback to aid in the hand guidance process.
